purpose: Extract Z3 contexts from H1-collapsed size-6 missing orbits in aut=6 manifolds and compute induced generator actions on the 3-class context (showing dihedral D6 structure).
findings: In both N12_54 and N12_57, there are multiple size-6 missing orbits that collapse to exactly 3 distinct H1 classes, each appearing twice (a natural 3×2 structure).
On each such context, the order-3 generator tau induces a 3-cycle on the three H1 classes.
The order-2 generator induces an order-2 permutation of the three classes and satisfies g2*tau*g2 = tau^{-1}, i.e., the class-level symmetry is dihedral D6.

anchor_pair.note: Anchor size-2 orbit triangles are disjoint and represent the same H1 class; tau fixes each and g2 swaps.
